The following are example programs that demonstrate Moby features.

----------------------------------------------------------------------

falling-ball.ss: a simple World program that shows a falling ball.

bubble-2.ss: a game that uses the tilt sensor to play a ball-rolling
game.

grocery-shopper.ss: an application that uses the GPS location 
feature and Google Maps web-service to alert the user when we're close
to an interesting grocery store.

location-announcer.ss: another GPS application that also uses SMS to
notify others of the place where a user is located.


bootstrap-game.ss: an example of a game that uses the simplified
Boostrap teachpack.
